Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as 8db83747b6ea72de30ac83f19578ecc37489b13d
Kind of wish we could use one, either "ssl" or "tls". oh well.

I changed everything internally to be TLS, I just didn't want to change the name of the option because that would break people.

I wonder if we should use the meson deprecated options, and have the deprecated option drive a new option?  not sure it's worth the effort.

FWIW, I changed SSL->TLS because I've more than once had the conversation with a security person that told us we were wrong for enabling SSL and it was outdated (even though the option really controls TLS).
not sure it's worth the effort. Low priority forsure.
Are these truly Critical?
It means that bmcweb can't handle ANY request from any user, so yeah, I think they're critical under the rules?  Right?
Acknowledged
Seems reasonable
